# Bilibili Login Support via SESSDATA

To allow downloading native Bilibili subtitles that require a logged-in user, we will add support for configuring a `SESSDATA` cookie.
To make it user-friendly, we will implement QR code login where the user can scan a QR code in the terminal to grant access, rather than manually hunting for the cookie.

## User Review Required
No breaking changes. The user will be able to configure `SESSDATA` via `--configure` or by directly editing `~/.bili-summary/config.yaml`.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] config.py
- Add a new [BilibiliConfig](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/config.py#21-24) class with a `sessdata` string field.
- Update [Config](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/config.py#41-76) class to include a `bilibili` field of type [BilibiliConfig](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/config.py#21-24).
- Update `Config.from_dict` and `ConfigManager.save` to serialize and deserialize the `bilibili` config.
- Update `ConfigManager.get_template` to mention the QR login flow or SESSDATA via config.

### Dependencies
#### [MODIFY] pyproject.toml
- Add `qrcode` to dependencies to render QR codes in the terminal.

### API Client
#### [MODIFY] bilibili.py
- Update `BilibiliAPI.__init__` to accept an optional `SESSDATA` string.
- If `SESSDATA` is provided, add it to the `httpx.AsyncClient` cookies.
- Add `generate_qr_code()` method.
- Add `poll_qr_code(qrcode_key)` method that returns the login status and, if successful, extracts SESSDATA from the response headers/cookies.

### CLI
#### [MODIFY] cli.py
- Update [process_video](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/cli.py#39-175) to instantiate [BilibiliAPI](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/bilibili.py#40-183) with `config.bilibili.sessdata`.
- Update the `--configure` flow in [main](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/cli.py#177-252) to generate a QR code, print it to the terminal, and poll until the user scans and confirms logic.
- Save the extracted `SESSDATA` to the config.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Update [tests/test_bilibili.py](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/tests/test_bilibili.py) and [tests/test_integration.py](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/tests/test_integration.py) to ensure [BilibiliAPI](file:///Users/zhangyifei/Code/bilibli-summary/bili_summary/bilibili.py#40-183) uses the `SESSDATA` correctly in its constructor.

### Manual Verification
- Run `bili-summary --configure` and ensure the QR code displays and polling occurs.
- Scan the code using the Bilibili app.
- Check `~/.bili-summary/config.yaml` to verify the `SESSDATA` is saved.
- Run `bili-summary BV1LmPazLEsX` and verify that it downloads the official subtitles.
